The paper proposes a new approach for generative modeling that can efficiently model data spaces with known invariances. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also mentions solving nonlinear partial differential equations (PDEs), which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses an adversarial training algorithm, which is a common technique in the field of generative modeling and suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
